FBIS3-39713 "drweu035aa_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Defense Ministers Meet at Aviano To Discuss Bosnia Italy Says News `Encouraging' LD2002150494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1437 GMT 20 Feb 94 LD2002150494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] [Italian] Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri said at a summit of five NATO defense ministers held in Aviano that "the decision of the international community to bring the Yugoslav crisis under control is now irreversible." As for the ultimatum, Fabbri said that "a full enforcement of the conditions set by the NATO order is required. There can be no bargains and no gifts. However, the news we received during our discussions is encouraging."
